  "templates": [
    {
      "id": "t1",
      "name": "#1 — First Contact",
      "subject": "Italian wines — proven in the US market",
      "body": "{{dear}}\n\nMy name is Luca Pattaro — I represent Siena Wine and Small Vineyards International, the global arm of Small Vineyards, a curated portfolio of Italian family wineries that has been successfully distributed across the United States for years through August Imports.\n\nWe are now bringing the same selection{{owner_mention}} — and the same operational model — to international markets.\n\nFor {{azienda}}, this means a single partner for a portfolio spanning Tuscany, Piedmont, Veneto, Sicily, Puglia and beyond: from Chianti Classico to Brunello, Barolo to Nero d'Avola.\n\nWould you have 20 minutes for a call this week?\n\nBest regards,\nLuca Pattaro\nExport Manager — Siena Wine | Small Vineyards International\nluca@sienawine.it | +39 331 1347899\nwww.sienawine.it"
    },
    {
      "id": "t2",
      "name": "#2 — Follow-up (day 7)",
      "subject": "One portfolio, all of Italy",
      "body": "{{dear}}\n\nFollowing up on my previous email — I wanted to share a bit more about what we offer.\n\nSmall Vineyards International brings together over 20 family-owned Italian producers, carefully selected and already performing well in the US market. The range covers virtually every major Italian wine region:\n\n• Tuscany: Chianti Classico, Brunello, Morellino di Scansano\n• Piedmont: Barolo, Barbera, Moscato\n• Veneto: Soave, Valpolicella, Prosecco\n• Sicily & South: Nero d'Avola, Primitivo, Negroamaro\n• And more to come.\n\nAll orders, documents, logistics and communication go through a single point of contact: us.\n\nHappy to send the full portfolio and price list — shall I?\n\nBest,\nLuca Pattaro\nSiena Wine | Small Vineyards International\nluca@sienawine.it | +39 331 1347899\nwww.sienawine.it"
    },
    {
      "id": "t3",
      "name": "#3 — Follow-up (day 21)",
      "subject": "One contact. One invoice. All of Italy.",
      "body": "{{dear}}\n\nWorking with multiple small Italian producers means multiple contacts, invoices, shipments and conversations. We solve that.\n\nThrough Siena Wine, {{azienda}} gets:\n\n✔ A single point of contact for the entire portfolio\n✔ Consolidated orders and shipments\n✔ Full documentation support\n✔ A selection proven to sell — validated by years of success in the US\n\nWe are not asking you to take a risk on unknown producers. These wines have a track record. We are simply making them available to you.\n\nWould you like to schedule a 20-minute call to see if there is a fit?\n\nBest,\nLuca Pattaro\nSiena Wine | Small Vineyards International\nluca@sienawine.it | +39 331 1347899\nwww.sienawine.it"
    },
    {
      "id": "t4",
      "name": "#4 — Break-up (day 35)",
      "subject": "Closing the loop — {{azienda}}",
      "body": "{{dear}}\n\nI have reached out a few times without hearing back — I completely understand, timing is everything in this business.\n\nI will not send further emails, but wanted to leave you with one thought: if you are ever looking to add a curated Italian portfolio with a proven US track record, a single operational contact, and wineries that genuinely over-deliver for their price point — we are here.\n\nYou can explore the portfolio anytime at www.sienawine.it\n\nWishing {{azienda}} continued success.\n\nLuca Pattaro\nSiena Wine | Small Vineyards International\nluca@sienawine.it | +39 331 1347899"
    }
